The first part of the course concentrates on introducing the reasons and possibilities of foreign market entry. Target market selection procedure and different foreign market entry methods (export, licensing, foreign investments) are introduced and main international marketing strategies are covered. After this the impact of economic, political and cultural differences on marketing mix standardization or differentiation decision is discussed. The second part of the course deals with managerial issues in international company and with differences that emerge in functional areas when company starts its business in international environment. As a result of this approach the students will during the lectures and seminars obtain the background knowledge needed for the internationalization of firm.  Case study analysis is extensively used during the course.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to develop the systematic approach how to arrange the internationalization of the firm.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students who pass the course: a) obtain knowledge about the fundamentals of the globalising economy b) are able to evaluate the impact of globalisation process on the selection of the strategy of internationalisation of firms c) know the models of internationalisation of firms d) are able to evaluate the importance of internationalization and its impact on their activities; e) know how to evaluate the influences of external environment on internationalization; f) are able to create plans for foreign market entry and to govern its execution; g) commands models of corporate governance used in managing internationalization of firms h) could apply the obtained knowledge in the specific firm (our collaborative partner)
